In my experience, full disk wipes on new laptops are justshort of absolutely neccessary.
With the amount of bloatware on them these days i definitely agree

Got a Dell Inspiron a few months ago, very fine laptop by all standards, but Dell puts soooo much damn bloatware that when I totally deleted that partition, it saw some serious gains in general performance. Especially at idle and especially on RAM.
And I still got the benefits of the software package by simply redeeming them right before the wipe and backing that information up.
